  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230ºC/ 210ºC (fan)/ gas 8</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Cut your<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into thick rings</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut a piece (or two!) of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or <strong>tin foil</strong>) approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>red onion rings</strong> and <strong>garlic clove[s] </strong>(skin on) in the middle of the baking paper piece[s], then transfer to a baking tray (or two!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cut a knob of <strong>butter</strong> into small cubes and dot them all over the potatoes</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the baking paper together around the potatoes to form a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Put the baking tray[s] in the oven for 40 min or until the potatoes are golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are in the oven, separate the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> from the <strong>white[s]</strong> by cracking your <strong>egg[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>over a small bowl and catching the yolk in the shell</p><p>Transfer the yolk from one shell half to the other several times, until all the whites are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell, then add the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Tip: Hold on to those egg whites! They're perfect for meringues or a protein-rich omelette (they freeze well too)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat, then add your <strong>crème fraîche</strong> and your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further, stirring constantly, or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Stir through the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your<strong> béarnaise sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have been in for 25 min, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>sirloin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, drizzle with<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides and once very hot, add the<strong> steak</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side then once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to wilt, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>béarnaise sauce</strong> to a very low heat and cook for 1 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-bearnaise-sauce-and-roasted-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak[s]</strong> finely on a clean board</p><p>Carefully cut the parcel[s] open and squeeze your <strong>garlic</strong> out of the skin</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced steak</strong> with the <strong>roasted potatoes</strong>,<strong> red onion rings, garlic</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon the<strong> béarnaise sauce</strong> over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
